subSubSection.paragraph:
Cephalothorax
: Carapace (
Fig. 16 A–C
) yellow, oval, slightly longer than wide, widest at coxae II and III; with a large brown and Y-shaped pattern (both lateral margins of pattern are wavelike lines) between ocular area and fovea; two pairs of spots near lateral margins of carapace; fovea inconspicuous. Sternum yellow. Labium yellowish brown. Chelicerae (
Fig. 19C, D
) yellowish brown and darker in apical half, with six promarginal peg teeth and two retromarginal teeth. Endites yellowish brown, longer than wide. Leg color similar to carapace, with irregular dark blotches.
